We need to pick out three items as follows:

• From the balance sheet we extract the “Capital contributed by shareholders in exchange for shares” which is shown by the line item “Paid-in Capital” and its end value.

• From the income statement we extract the “profit or loss for a period before deducting tax expense” which is given by the line “Profit Before Tax.”

• From the cash flow statement (which reports changes in working capital items) we extract “the addition in the amount owed by the entity for goods or services received or purchased on credit during the period.” In the statement this is shown as “Increase (Decrease) in Accounts Payable.”

Looking at the provided tables:

1. In the balance sheet the “Paid-in Capital” end value is 13000000.00.

2. In the income statement the “Profit Before Tax” value is 1337664.61.

3. In the cash flow statement the “Increase (Decrease) in Accounts Payable” amount is 462000.00.

Following the specified order: first item from the balance sheet, then income statement, and finally from the cash flow statement, the final answer is:
